recipes.title: SAMBAAR
recipes.description:
Heres a step-by-step guide to prepare authentic Kerala Sambar:

 Ingredients

(Serves 45 people)

Vegetables:

Drumstick  1 stick (cut into 2-inch pieces)

Brinjal (Eggplant)  1 medium (cubed)

Ash gourd   cup (cubed)

Carrot  1 medium (sliced)

Ladies finger (Okra)  45 pieces

Tomato  1 large (chopped)

Shallots (Small onions)  68

Green chilies  2 slit

Curry leaves  2 sprigs

Other Ingredients:

Toor dal (pigeon peas)   cup

Tamarind  1 lemon-sized ball (soaked in warm water)

Sambar powder  23 tbsp

Turmeric powder   tsp

Salt  to taste

Jaggery   tsp (optional for balance)

For tempering:

Coconut oil  2 tbsp

Mustard seeds   tsp

Dried red chilies  2

Fenugreek seeds   tsp

Curry leaves  a few

Asafoetida  a pinch

 Preparation Steps
1. Cook the dal

Wash  cup toor dal well.

Pressure cook with 2 cups water,  tsp turmeric, and a few drops of oil until soft (34 whistles).

Mash well and keep aside.

2. Prepare tamarind extract

Soak tamarind in  cup warm water for 1015 min.

Squeeze and extract the juice. Keep aside.

3. Cook vegetables

In a pot, add drumstick, carrot, ash gourd, brinjal, shallots, green chilies, curry leaves.

Add  tsp turmeric, salt, and enough water to cook.

Cook until vegetables are soft but not mushy.

4. Add sambar powder and tamarind

Once veggies are cooked, add 23 tbsp sambar powder, tamarind extract, and chopped tomato.

Simmer for 57 minutes until raw smell of tamarind and spice goes away.

5. Add cooked dal

Add mashed dal to the pot.

Mix well, add water as needed to get a medium-thick consistency.

Simmer for 510 minutes. Check salt.

Add a small piece of jaggery (optional) for flavor balance.

6. Prepare tempering (thaalikkal)

Heat 2 tbsp coconut oil in a small pan.

Add  tsp mustard seeds, let them splutter.

Add dried red chilies,  tsp fenugreek seeds, curry leaves, and a pinch of asafoetida.

Pour this over the sambar and mix.

7. Serve

Kerala Sambar tastes best with hot rice, pappadam, and a drizzle of ghee.
